Monthly inter-dimensional techno and rhythm transmissions from GiGi FM.
From the host: "On this month’s episode, GiGi FM welcomes Berlin-based Floral.
An emotion-forward mix exploring love and rupture, yearning, and light found in darkness ~ aligned with January’s Aquarian shift and the Leo Full Moon."_

nts1.n: A LONG STRANGE DREAM W/ BATU
nts1.d:
A Long Strange Dream is Batu's latest series which allows him to showcase a selection of music not limited to peak time dancefloors. Expect a deep dive into the crates for an eclectic mix of influences and oddities as you transcend into a collective long strange dream.
From the host: "Deep January listening inspired by David Toop's Ocean of Sound."

Uruguay DJ, producer and sound designer Lechuga Zafiro presents his radio show: CDJ explorations in South American dance music, field recording related music and beyond. Played live.
From the host: "recorded live at a show in Casa Montjuic, Barcelona Jan 10 with 4 cdjs and a djm 900.
a current expression of the confusing times we live in. bits from films, experimental music, a lot of silence, mexican metal, frenetic rhythms."

nts1.n: IN FOCUS: RAMONA ANDRA LANGLEY / VEKTROID (R)
nts1.d: Producing under a slew of faceless and corporate-sounding pseudonyms, Ramona Andra Langley – aka Vektroid, aka Macintosh Plus, aka New Dreams Ltd, aka PrismCorp Virtual Enterprises… you get the picture – is a vital figure in the development and popularisation of vaporwave music. As prolific as ever, Langley's contemporary work continues to develop hand in glove with the the peculiar trends and idiosynchracies of the post-internet era.
Irish avant pop artist Maria Somerville traverses heady concepts through classic pop, ambient, experimental, spoken word, & field recordings - now hosted ever morning for the NTS Breakfast Show here.

Veteran NTS host Hampus brings you Doing Time: a genre-agnostic monthly trip through quality records from around the world’s past and present, featuring regular appearances from musical friends and family.

From the host: "Post-punk in Peru emerged mainly within the framework of Rock Subterráneo, a movement that took shape in the mid-1980s on the margins of official circuits. Bands inspired by post-punk currents circulating globally forged, from their own social realities, a language that combined introspection, experimentation, and social critique. More than a mood, Peruvian post-punk expressed a collective sensibility shaped by the violence and precariousness that afflicted the country, turning that unrest into a form of creation and affirmation within the local underground."

Considered a reaction to the more lively bebop styles of jazz, the postwar era saw a rise in subdued styles, often referencing classical music. NTS selects two hours of cool jazz from Miles Davis, Chet Baker and more.

A unique dip into the musical history of Ukraine with archival label Shukai, journeying back to the ‘90s, playing music from documentaries, sci-fi films, obscure cartoons and late-night music programming, curated by Dmytro Nikolaienko, Dmytro Prutkin and Alec Tsapenko.
From the host: "Step inside the sonic laboratory of Soviet Ukraine’s Kyivnaukfilm (Eng: Kyiv Science Film, active years 1941-1993) studio — a workshop where composers and sound designers crafted scores for documentary, science, education, and animation films. From eerie synth textures to inventive tape collages, these rare recordings (1967–1990) reveal a secret world of avant-garde music created under censorship yet brimming with experiments."

subtle.d: Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
